examples.en: The writer's humor animates the novel.
A writer's style must develop organically.
A few of the writer's journals have resurfaced.
The writer's house has become a shrine to his fans.
It's a writer's prerogative to decide the fate of her characters.
The purpose of the book seems clean gone out of the writer's mind.
The biography includes conjectures about the writer's earliest ambitions.
I recognized the writer's distinctive phraseology even before I saw the name.
After his second novel Garland had writer's block (=he could not write anything).
The writer's latest memoir is a seemingly unending exercise in narcissistic rambling.
The writer's descriptions are objectively expositive and entirely without editorialization.
